{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, the control group displayed an exacerbation in depression scores following the intervention, signifying the potentially deleterious consequences of refraining from participation in cardiac rehabilitation post-cardiac event.",
    "Crucially, the exercise groups managed to preserve lower levels of anxiety and depression during the 6-and 12-month follow-up evaluations.",
    "Among patients with low-risk CAD, both HIIT and MICT exercise programs led to significant enhancements in BMI, body fat percentage, total body fat mass, percentage of abdominal fat, WC, and VO 2 peak.",
    "The HIIT group additionally exhibited a substantial improvement in maximal knee extensor strength.",
    "Importantly, following the culmination of the community-based exercise CR program, these improvements were largely sustained over time, with only two significant variations observed: a reduction in WC after 6 months in the HIIT group and a significant decline in maximal knee flexor strength in the MICT group after 12 months."
  ]
}